Defendant Kathryn M Rosio in court with attorney Michael L. Chernin.  Brandon Wigley on behalf of Paul M. Hauer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: KAR.
Case calendared for sentencing hearing.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1 -

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 36 MONTHS, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 0 (zero) days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 18 MONTHS.  

COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed defendant on probation for 18 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
- Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment.
- Defendant to participate in mental health evalution and successfully complete recommended treatment.
- Defendant to notify Department of Corrections agent of all prescriptions received from medical professional.
- Follow all rules set forth by the probation agent.
- No further violations of the law rising to the level of probable cause.
- Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge, during the course of probation to the probation agent. Any remaining balance due at the end of probation will become immediately due or civil judgment to be entered. 
- Fine is set at ZERO.
- Provide DNA sample, if not already done. 

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant.

Defendant Kathryn M Rosio in court with attorney Michael L. Chernin.  Paul M. Hauer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: tmk.
Case set for final pretrial. Parties have reached a resolution and proceeded to plea hearing.
AS TO COUNT 1:
Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised she is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms. Defendant is advised she is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored. Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court vacated jury trial on May 27, 2015. Sentencing hearing scheduled for July 23, 2015 at 08:30 am.
